> a
> diesel 3/4 ton Chevy beater I picked up, I was struck as always by that old
> VW
> smell.  Nothing is like it, and I wondered what it is from, because even
> late
> air cooled (vanagons) don't have it.  Doesn't matter if bus, bug, thing,
> ghia
> (I've had em all) even a bit the 914 though not as much, it is there.  You
> get
> in and it is immediately familiar, like a friendly old memory.  I have
> always
> presumed that it is mostly the smell of years of oil baked into heater
> boxes.
> I don't recall off the top of my head if the last "stale air" car I had (a
> bug) had the same smell or not, and more or less if it did (been 20 years
> since I owned that car,) I presume it was worse, more burnt oil smelling.
>  I
> know my buddies Covair Monza spyder "Chevy stale air heater" does not have
> the
> same odor.  It occurs to me,
>  perhaps not only oil and combustion by products, but VW vinyl mixing with
> decrepit horse hair padding, because the smell definitely permeates the
> horse
> hair when you re-do a seat, and would explain why vanagons with that pesky
> foam stuff in most of the cushions don't have it as much.  I always
> presumed
> it was the smell that had permeated the horse hair, maybe it is the other
> way
> round.  Anyway I love the smell, seemed like a good Friday topic.
>
> Discuss, if anyone is out there anymore.
